<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-028-284 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 470 981</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 28 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Novadyne buys maintenance firm Omnibit. (Novadyne Computer Systems)(Omnibit Computer Systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novadyne Computer Systems Inc. (Acquisitions, mergers,divestments)Omnibit Computer Systems (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments).andO;Topic:     Computer ServicesAcquisitionThird-Party Vendors.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Novadyne Buys Maintenance Firm Omnibit 10/28/91 TORONTO, ONTARIO, CANADA,1991 OCT 28 (NB) -- Independent maintenance vendor Novadyne Computer Systems,of Santa Ana, California, has bought Omnibit Computer Systems, which providesthird-party maintenance for Canadian users of Tandem, Digital Equipment, andData General computers.andM;Novadyne the largest independent maintenance provider for Tandem equipment inthe United States, said the deal will let it offer comprehensive hardwareservices for Tandem users throughout North America.andP;  Omnibit will operate asa wholly owned subsidiary of Novadyne, keeping its present name.andP;  Founder DanCrook will remain as president.andM;Novadyne's inventory of spare parts, repair centers, and technical supportservices will also be made available to Omnibit.andM;The two companies have had a joint service agreement since September, 1990,serving customers with Tandem equipment in both the United States and Canada.andO;For three years, Novadyne has also provided Omnibit with technical support,field engineer training, and other services.andM;Omnibit, founded in 1987, has offices in Toronto, Ottawa, and Vancouver.andO;Novadyne has more than 1,000 employees in some 125 locations.andP;  Revenues in1990 exceeded $104 million.andM;(Grant Buckler/19911028/Press Contact: Pat Dwight, Novadyne Computer Systems,714-566-3717)</TEXT></DOC>